The capital city is Bangar. Temburong is an exclave. It is separated from the rest of Brunei by Malaysia and Brunei Bay. The Temburong River flows through the district, and the Sungai Pandaruan river forms the western border. Brunei's first national park, the Ulu Temburong National Park, is in the south of the Temburong district. Temburong is divided into five mukim (subdistricts): * Amo * Bangar * Batu Apoi * Bokok * Labu ==References== Category:Districts of Brunei
